title: Malaysia Current Account
description: Malaysia recorded a Current Account surplus of 14136 MYR Million in the third quarter of 2022. Current Account in Malaysia averaged 14824.68 MYR Million from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 39982 MYR Million in the third quarter of 2008 and a record low of 978 MYR Million in the second quarter of 2013. Current Account is the sum of the balance of trade (exports minus imports of goods and services), net factor income (such as interest and dividends) and net transfer payments (such as foreign aid). This page provides - Malaysia Current Account - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Department of Statistics, Malaysia
